716461f-a.text:
(1)
Barclay Street (right), south side, west from West Broadway
(foreground) to West Street. Shown on Greenwich Street is the Ninth
Ave. Elevated structure. At the left are buildings that bear West
Broadway numbers. The huge edifice apparent in the background is the
New York Telephone Building, No. 140 West Street.
July 26, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, slightly more inclusive. The three buildings on the
left being Nos. 14 to 10 West Broadway and 229 to 225 Greenwich Street;
being units that continue through the block.
May 11, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
